<TEXT>
a man convicted of raping and maiming 
a teenager almost 10 years ago is seeking a criminal investigation 
into his allegation that the woman actually kidnapped him a 
newspaper reported monday 
lawrence singleton who is scheduled to be freed april 25 after 
serving seven years and nine months in prison and a year on parole 
said he filed a complaint in superior court in placer and marin 
counties requesting the womans arrest the daily ledger of antioch 
reported 
singleton 60 was convicted in 1979 of raping mary vincent 
then 15 and hacking off her forearms with an ax on sept 29 1978 
he was sentenced to 14 years and 4 months in prison which was 
reduced for good behavior and work credit 
singleton said he will move to oregon to spend his first few 
days of freedom with a church group after his release the 
newspaper said but he did not rule out a return to california 
singleton has spent the last 10 months of his parole in a 
trailer on the grounds of san quentin state prison for his own 
protection after residents of several northern california 
communities protested against his planned parole last year 
vincent who expressed anxiety about his parole at that time 
has moved to the pacific northwest and recently told the associated 
press through an intermediary that she did not want to be 
interviewed further about singleton 
the ledger said it obtained a copy of a 12page typewritten 
complaint in which singleton alleges vincent committed kidnap for 
the purpose of robbery and use of two deadly weapons 
according to the ledger the complaint said singleton was 
heading to sparks nev when he picked up vincent hitchhiking in 
berkeley calif and agreed to take her to reno 
the complaint said vincent began smoking pcp a hallucinogen 
then said she wanted to go to los angeles became abusive and poked 
singleton with a threefoot surveyor stick the newspaper reported 
she told me that if i did not comply with her wishes she 
would poke out my eyes smash my face and hurt hurt hurt me and 
say that i raped her the newspaper quoted the complaint as 
saying 
the complaint also alleges vincent threatened singleton with a 
sixinch fishscaling knife the newspaper reported 
singleton claims he drove vincent to galt 20 miles south of 
sacramento where he picked up two male hitchhikers who joined 
vincent in extorting money from singleton to buy drugs the 
newspaper reported 
the complaint says singleton drove north and left vincent in a 
lowrent district in sacramento and never saw her again the 
newspaper reported 
although not in the complaint singleton has repeatedly claimed 
he allowed one of the hitchhikers to drive while he was drinking 
passed out then awoke to find vincent was gone but her clothes 
were still in the van 
the hitchhikers he has contended committed the crimes 
authorities however have maintained the two hitchhikers never 
existed 
singleton said in a telephone interview he mailed the complaint 
saturday to authorities in the two counties but court clerks in 
both counties said monday morning they had not received the 
complaints the ledger reported 
</TEXT>
