<TEXT>
a boater who spent 12 days drifting 
in the gulf of mexico without food or water wanted to see his 
5yearold daughter before he died but perished hours before 
rescuers arrived said a friend who survived 
timothy daniels 19 describing the ordeal shared by him and 
jimmie lee thacker from his hospital bed in this gulf coast city on 
monday said he had daydreams about grape soda and ice cream while 
adrift 
daniels who was rescued saturday was in stable condition today 
after being moved out of the intensive care unit at seven rivers 
community hospital he was being treated for hypothermia sunburn 
starvation and dehydration said a nursing supervisor who asked 
that her name not be used 
thacker 25 died late friday or early saturday 
all i know is that he wanted to see his little girl again 
before he died said daniels a shrimper thacker was separated 
from his wife and 5yearold girl who live in virginia 
the ordeal began march 28 when daniels and thacker went to 
anclote key an island north of tarpon springs in a 14foot skiff 
with two friends 
at dusk daniels and thacker left the island to get matches and 
more soft drinks they never came back 
their friends got back to the mainland the next morning by 
hitching a ride from a passing fisherman and told family members 
about the disappearence prompting a coast guard search the next 
day the searchers gave up a week later 
daniels said the shore was out of sight when the boat lost 
power they drifted south and west and lost their bearings 
all he and thacker had to drink were two bottles of pepsi which 
they emptied the first night so they could use them to bail out the 
boat after it was drenched by 16foot waves 
i didnt use my head i freaked out daniels said i could 
have used the engine cover to bail 
desperate for water daniels daydreamed and used saltwater to 
rinse his mouth he said he spent much of his time praying 
on several occasions porpoises came to the boat and lifted 
their snouts apparently to see if the men had any fish for them 
seeing the porpoises made me feel better daniels said 
when they had been adrift for several days a big shrimp boat 
came into view 
believing help had finally come daniels picked up the engine 
box and began waving it frantically to get the other boats 
attention i was yelling and hollering at the top of my lungs and 
everything he said 
but the other boat didnt approach 
it just kept going daniels said one person on board 
raised his hand and waved as the boat pulled away 
daniels was rescued when a charter boat spotted him 14 miles 
west of crystal river 
despite his experience he said hes looking forward to getting 
back to work on the gulf 
its my home away from home daniels said its how i make 
my living 
