vigilance and patrol said pentagon spokesman dan howard 
the purpose of the intrusions and the exact identity of the 
intruders were not clear he said 
the facility stores fuel for us airplanes and vehicles at 
nearby howard air force base he said 
when one has intruders into the base perimeter who are in 
uniform and are camouflaged the assumption that one comes to is 
that of course they are pdf or members of the panamanian 
defense force said howard 
no intruders were apprehended in the confusion of the firing 
the intruders all escaped said us air force col ron sconyers 
a spokesman at us southern command 
the marine was identified as cpl ricardo m villahermosa 25 
of santurce puerto rico he was part of i company 3rd battalion 
4th marine regiment part of the 6th marine expeditionary brigade 
and was sent from camp lejeune nc to panama as part of a 
strengthened security force last week officials said 
villahermosa was struck by at least one shot in the abdomen and 
was pronounced dead at gorgas hospital in panama 
attempts to revive the marine with openheart massage were 
unsuccessful several major arteries were hit by the bullet and the 
marine suffered massive internal bleeding sconyers said 
describing the incident as a tragic accident howard told 
reporters at the pentagon that it occurred after an apparent 
intrusion by six or eight individuals into the tank farm area 
us security forces patrolling the area split up and were in 
the process of rejoining when a trip flare was set off sounding 
like gunfire he said 
in response two elements of the patrol fired seven rounds 
were discharged before the onthescene commander ordered a 
ceasefire initial indications are that the fatal gunshot wound was 
not the result of hostile gunfire but rather the result of a 
crossfire from the us shots fired he said 
details of the incident are sketchy at this time he said 
and the matter is under investigation 
in another accident two us army uh60a blackhawk helicopters 
carrying a total of eight soldiers collided during a night training 
exercise at an airstrip at fort sherman in panama howard said 
the soldiers were conducting routine training involving 
familiarization with nightvision devices immediately prior to the 
crash at about 1045 pm edt monday night said the spokesman 
the soldiers assigned to the first battalion 228 aviation 
regiment in panama were treated for minor injuries he said 
the accident came just over a month after two uh60 helicopters 
collided during a night training mission and crashed 250 feet to 
the ground killing 17 servicemen near fort campbell army air field 
in kentucky 
the blackhawk is one of the armys newest helicopters but has 
been grounded several times last summer officials said that about 
40 people had been killed in crashes of the helicopter since 1978 
