senate democratic leader robert c byrd 
announced tuesday he will not seek reelection to the party post he 
has held for a dozen years touching off a wideopen race to 
succeed him 
the 70yearold west virginian said he will run for a sixth 
senate term and if elected and the chamber remains under 
democratic control assume the chairmanship of the senate 
