here are some comparative facts about israel 
when the country was founded and now 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
israels population 
israels population in 1948 according to government statistics 
was 872700 including 716700 jews and in 1949 was 1173900 
including 1013900 jews the population in 1988 is 4331300 of 
whom 3561400 are jews 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
population of west bank and gaza 
there were 585900 in the west bank when israel captured it from 
jordan in 1967 and the population is 836000 in 1988 in gaza 
which belonged to egypt the population was 380800 in 1967 and is 
545000 in 1988 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
immigration 
the number of immigrants to israel was 170200 in 1950 but by 
1988 had declined to 9500 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
economy 
israels gross national product was 128 billion in 1950 and 
3137 billion in 1988 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
area 
including east jerusalem and the golan heights which have been 
annexed israels area is 13330 square miles there are 2126 
square miles in the west bank and 140 in the gaza strip 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
military 
defense expenditures have increased from 1025 million in 1948 
to 43 billion in 1988 the military has grown in size from 34000 
personnel to 170000 with 370000 reservists 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
leaders 
