<TEXT>
western union corp will lay off 
about 1800 workers some 25 percent of its work force by the end 
of this year as part of its financial restructuring the company 
said tuesday 
robert j amman president and chief executive officer also 
said the company had established five separate business units under 
the restructuring 
western unions restructuring plan completed dec 30 included 
the 178 million acquisition of itt world communications inc an 
exchange of debt for stock and the borrowing of about 500 million 
through the sale of highinterest debentures 
the plan was aimed at helping keep the communications company 
afloat after years of major financial losses western union 
officials have said that without the restructuring the company 
would have had to file for bankruptcy protection 
the layoffs will affect workers in all parts of the combined 
company spokesman warren bechtel said 
amman said in a news release that the creation of separate 
business units to operate on a standalone basis and the 
integration of itt world communications into western union are 
the first steps in implementing our strategic plan to make the 
company more profitable 
the business largest unit business communications services 
oversees the companys international and domestic telex and 
electronic mail service 
money transfer services and mailgram and telegram message 
services are handled by another division the consumer 
communications and financial services unit will coordinate the 
nationwide network of 11000 western union agents and the companys 
centralized telephone bureaus 
a third division priority mail services is responsible for 
commercial mailgram messages priority letters and computer letters 
to business and special interest groups 
western unions advanced transmission systems supervises 
construction and operation of local and regional fiber optic 
transmission facilities for corporate customers and other 
communications carriers 
the fifth unit is responsible for national marketing of western 
unions long distance and leased transmission servicees along with 
the companys international leased line business and satellite 
service 
western union earned 881 million in 1987 on revenue of 802 
million bechtel said 
